    <h1>What is Llama 4? The Absolute Beginner's Guide to the World’s Most Powerful Free AI</h1>
    <p class="lead">Forget everything you thought you knew about "expensive" AI. Llama 4 has arrived, and it is changing the rules of the digital world for everyone, everywhere.</p>

    <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1677442136019-21780ecad995?auto=format&fit=crop&q=80&w=1200" alt="Artificial Intelligence Neural Network" class="featured-image">

    <h2>1. The Dawn of the "People's AI"</h2>
    <p>In the early days of the AI boom, access to high-level intelligence was hidden behind paywalls and subscriptions. If you wanted the "smartest" version of a chatbot, you had to pay. <strong>Meta’s Llama 4</strong> has officially broken that cycle. </p>
    <p>Released in April 2025 and matured through 2026, Llama 4 isn't just a program; it's a massive shift in how technology is shared. By releasing the "weights" (the brain's blueprints) for free, Meta has allowed every person with an internet connection to access a tool that rivals—and often beats—the most expensive systems in the world.</p>

    <div class="video-card">
        <div class="video-info">
            <h3>🎥 Watch: Llama 4 in Action</h3>
            <p>If you prefer a visual walkthrough, check out this excellent breakdown of how to access and use the Llama family right now.</p>
            <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=FE7-JvKKHkI" target="_blank" class="btn-play">Watch on YouTube</a>
        </div>
    </div>

    <h2>2. Understanding the "Herd": Scout, Maverick, and Behemoth</h2>
    <p>Llama 4 is designed as a family. Instead of one giant, slow program, Meta created three specific versions for different needs. Think of them as the three types of vehicles in a fleet:</p>
    
    <div class="info-grid">
        <div class="info-card">
            <h4>Llama 4 Scout</h4>
            <p>The "Commuter Car." It’s small, incredibly fast, and can run on a single high-end computer. Despite its size, it has an "infinite memory" (10 million tokens), allowing it to read 20 books at once without forgetting the first page.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="info-card">
            <h4>Llama 4 Maverick</h4>
            <p>The "All-Terrain SUV." This is the general assistant. It understands text and **images** natively. You can show it a photo of a messy room and ask it for a cleaning plan, or a screenshot of a bug in your code, and it will fix it.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <h2>3. The Technical Magic: "Mixture of Experts" (MoE)</h2>
    <p>How is Llama 4 so fast? It uses a revolutionary design called **Mixture of Experts**. Imagine walking into a giant library with 100 experts. In old AI models, every single expert had to wake up and talk to answer one question. In Llama 4, the system only wakes up the 2 experts who know the answer to your specific question.</p>
    <p>This makes the AI much more "energy-efficient." It's better for the planet and faster for your phone battery.</p>

    <h2>4. Native Multimodality: The AI Can "See"</h2>
    <p>One of the biggest hurdles for beginners was that AI could only "read" text. Llama 4 changed that by being **natively multimodal**. </p>
    <p>This means the AI was taught to see and read at the same time. If you upload a complex graph from a financial report, Llama 4 Maverick doesn't just guess what's in it—it truly "understands" the relationship between the numbers and the visual lines. This is a massive resource for researchers and students who deal with visual data every day.</p>

    <h2>5. How This Helps You (No Matter Where You Are)</h2>
    <p>Whether you are in New York, London, Kampala, or Sydney, Llama 4 offers the same level of assistance. Here is how people are using it today:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Education:</strong> Translating complex scientific papers into 12 different languages instantly.</li>
        <li><strong>Business:</strong> Automating customer support replies that actually sound human and helpful.</li>
        <li><strong>Creativity:</strong> Generating high-quality outlines for blogs, books, and scripts in seconds.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Summary: Why Llama 4 Matters</h2>
    <p>Llama 4 is more than just a tech update. It is a tool of **democratization**. It ensures that the most powerful technology in human history isn't just for the 1%, but for the 100%. By being open-weight, free-to-use, and incredibly smart, it is the ultimate "Quick Resource" for the modern world.</p>
    
